    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 19.8,
      "end": 20.94,
      "text": "Isab's fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.68,
      "end": 24.88,
      "text": "The monkey as king.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.78,
      "end": 33.7,
      "text": "At a gathering of all the animals, the monkey danced and delighted them so much that they made him their king.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.8,
      "end": 39.46,
      "text": "The fox, however, was very much disgusted at the promotion of the monkey.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.38,
      "end": 46.92,
      "text": "So, having one day found a trap with a piece of meat in it, he took the monkey there and said to him,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 47.46,
      "end": 55.46,
      "text": "here is a dainty morsel I have found, Sire, I did not take it myself because I thought it ought to be reserved for you, our king.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 56.56,
      "end": 58.36,
      "text": "Will you be pleased to accept it?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 59.7,
      "end": 63.46,
      "text": "The monkey made it once for the meat and got caught in the trap.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 64.74,
      "end": 71.14,
      "text": "Then he bitterly reproached the fox for leading him into danger, but the fox only laughed and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 71.14,
      "end": 77.9,
      "text": "Oh, monkey, you call yourself king of the beasts and haven't more sense than to be taken in like that.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 80.08,
      "end": 82.06,
      "text": "End of The Monkey as King.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
